<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1610,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName box="[151,276,1610,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,276,1610,1634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Platypygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other genera of Platypyginae by the combination of following characters: postgena not developed as an acute process; mesonotum highly arched; discal cell closed and presence of vein R 
<number box="[1383,1391,1661,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1401,1408,1661,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
at the middle of veins R 
<number box="[392,400,1697,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[409,416,1697,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="5.0">5</number>
and R 
<number box="[489,497,1697,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
(i.e., its apex is equidistant between the end of both veins).
</paragraph>
